<p>James K. Polk, the 11th president of the United States, was born on 11/2/1795, in Mecklenburg County, North Carolina. He was 49 when he took office on 3/4/1845. Member: Democratic Party.

	
		He left office on 3/4/1849.
	

	His occupation before the presidency: Lawyer.
	His college: University of North Carolina.

	
		He died in Nashville, Tennessee, on 6/15/1849.
	
</p>

